<subSubSection id="C32E65595CD0FF7448A6FD6BFE11FC35" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25CD0FF7448A6FD6BFE11FC35" blockId="207.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CD0FF7448A6FD6BFEF5FD30" bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CD0FF744AF3FD6BFCE1FD30" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[658,815,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CD0FF744AF3FD6BFCE1FD30" box="[658,815,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">A. breviramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body with darkish blue reflection and the metapectal-propodeal disc black; the median clypeal carina higher than frons level; the paraspiracular carina present and conspicuous; the metasomal segments glabrous; the paramere longer than the basiparamere and very slender, almost filiform; and the aedeagus with the basal portion wide and the apical portion slender and as long as the basal portion, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CD0FF7449A5FC9BFDACFCA0" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[452,610,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CD0FF7449A5FC9BFDACFCA0" box="[452,610,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">A. breviramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body black; the median clypeal carina lower than frons level; the paraspiracular carina present and inconspicuous; the metasomal segments sparsely setose; the paramere longer than the basiparamere and bifid; and the aedeagus with basal portion slender, and the apical portion very slender and longer than the basal portion.
</paragraph>
